
[1]rigorously

   RIG'OROUSLY, adv.

   1. Severely; without relaxation, abatement or mitigation; as a sentence
   rigorously executed.

   2. Strictly; exactly; with scrupulous nicety; rigidly.

   The people would examine his works more vigorously than himself.
